                    <h2 class="h4 mb-0">How to Use a Template</h2>
                </div>

                <p class="text-muted mb-3">
                    Templates are applied on the <strong>Add Activities</strong> page (the step after creating a session), under the <strong>Template</strong> tab — not on the Create Session page itself.
                </p>

                <div class="bg-light p-4 rounded mb-3">
                    <h6 class="fw-semibold mb-2">Steps:</h6>
                    <ol class="mb-0 text-muted">
                        <li>Create a session (title, description, join form)</li>
                        <li>On the <strong>Add Activities</strong> page, click the <strong>Template</strong> tab</li>
                        <li>Filter by category or browse all 22 templates</li>
                        <li>Click a template card to preview the activities it contains</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>Add Activities</strong> — they are appended to your activity list</li>
                        <li>Edit, reorder, or delete individual activities, then <strong>Save Session</strong></li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <div class="alert alert-success border-0 mb-0">
                    <i class="fas fa-lightbulb me-2"></i>
                    <small><strong>Tip:</strong> Template activities are <em>added</em> to whatever you already have — they don't replace existing activities. You can combine multiple templates or mix with manual activities.</small>
